If we have closed bidding: player A and player B send a tell to ML that they are interested, ML announces &quot;2 players, A has 10 points, B has 11 points, send tell with your bid now&quot;. Player A only bids 2 points because this item would be a minor upgrade, player B wants this item badly, so he bids all his 11 points - does he really lose all 11 points then?<br>
Same scenario but only player C is interested in the item, ML announces &quot;only player C sent me a tell, the item goes to player C for the minimum of 2 points&quot;. So player C was just lucky that no one else was there who wanted that drop, while player B lost all his points though 4 (if increasing in steps of 2) would have been enough. Seems a bit unfair to me but maybe you can change my point of view <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Lildariel Silberwolf<br> Woodelf Hierophant 60th season<br> Officer of Heroes of Kaladim</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bscarab5467.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goldarkstormwind>Goldark Stormwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/9/02 11:14 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://the-fellowship.port5.com/images/goldark_head.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Open or hidden bidding during loot auctions?</span><hr size=1> With closed bidding I don't think there's any intention to announce how many points each person has.<br>
