<br>
Player A has 10pts, player B 11pts<br>
<br>
Player A bids 2pts, player B bids 11 pts<br>
<br>
The item goes to Player B for 3pts (he bid the most but gets the item for the minimum number of points needed to win).<br>
<br>
This way the person who really wants the item still gets it, but does not sacrifice a huge number of points to get it. If both players really wanted the item and bid all their points then player B pays the 11 points, chances are the items would have to be fairly uber for this to happen. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=186665">Thug - 60 War</A>
