<br>
Only one example:<br>
<br>
Player A has 5 pts, B 14PTS<br>
<br>
Open Bid<br>
Item one A and B are bidding.<br>
A bids 5 B; bids 6<br>
<br>
Item two A and B are bidding<br>
A bids 5, B 6<br>
<br>
Close is explaining herself.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Closed Bidding is fairer for me because you bid only so many RPs, which the item is wort for you. Only one exception if there is only one bidder, RPs cost should reduce to a minimum RPs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bscarab5467.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whirleyblades>WhirleyBlades</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/4/03 3:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Open or hidden bidding during loot auctions?</span><hr size=1> I think open bidding is fairer,<br>
As it lets a person that has done more raids without ever collecting anything put into the bid what they think the item is worth to them, but where no one else is interested in the item, they dont overpay for what the item is worth<br>
And in the case of where two or more people are interested it means that the people that have put more into raiding with Scarab have the choice of whether they want to pay for that item or let it go.<br>
So that person A who has 22 points can decide to bit upto that limit to buy the item<br>
And person B who has 12 points can bid upto 12<br>
In a closed bid person a might decide 10 points is enough to get the item so bids that wheras person B bids all 12 of his so person A looses out even though they really wanted the item. At least in an open bid he can decide that its worth putting more into his bid to make sure that he gets the item, and as they have done more raiding with scarab that is only fair, and person B will have to wait that little longer Just like person A has done in the first place to get all those extra RP.<br>
RP are an indicator of how many raids a person has done so it is only right they should get the option to get an item if they want it.<br>
If a person is found to over bid on their RPs then I suggest that that person looses alll their RPs anyway and that that cost is deducted from the next closest bidders costs (be they higher or lower) Thus in this case at time making this item free to the person that wins<br>
